# GitHub push account

This repo (`github.com/muditmittal/dbui`) belongs to the `muditmittal` personal GitHub account. Pushes from the `mudit-mittal_data` enterprise account fail with HTTP 403 `Permission denied`.

## Before any `git push`

Ensure the active `gh` account is `muditmittal`:

```bash
gh auth status        # read-only check
gh auth switch --user muditmittal   # only if active account is something else
git push origin <branch>
```

## If a push fails with 403

Symptom:
```
remote: Permission to muditmittal/dbui.git denied to mudit-mittal_data.
fatal: ... The requested URL returned error: 403
```

Fix: run `gh auth switch --user muditmittal` and retry the push. Do not edit the remote URL, credential helper, or global git config.

## Do NOT

- Do not push with `mudit-mittal_data` (enterprise account — no access to this repo)
- Do not prompt the user to re-authenticate if both accounts are already listed in `gh auth status`
- Do not swap to SSH or change `origin` — the HTTPS remote is correct, only the active `gh` identity matters
